;// New Simulation Parameters for RF MOS Devices                        // 
;//                                                                     // 
;//                                                                     // 
;/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

*Unless specified, these parameters are found on all rf mos devices.

1) ngcon: Enables single vs double gate contact model.  Default value is 1.

SBC18* -To make the field viewable and editable, set the RDS_DISPLAY_NGCON 
environment variable to t and restart cadence.  Value can be set to 1 or 2
for pre-layout simulations.  The layout pcell only supports single gate
contacts (1).
EX: setenv RDS_DISPLAY_NGCON t

CA18 -When the gate connection is set to "None", "Top", "Bottom",
or "Alternate", the netlisted value is 1 and for the "Both" case 
the value is 2.

2) hf_noise: Choosing 0 or 1 disables/enables the high frequency 
noise model.  The default value is 0.  Available only on the 1.8V rf nmos.

3) ring_sub: Models the effects of a 2 vs 4 sided substrate ring generated by 
the pcell.  "0" represents the 2 sided substrate ring (lr) and "1" represents
the 4 sided substrate ring (lbrt).  If the layout does not contain either
case, then pre-layout simulations will not accurately model the selected tap
option.  Default value is 1.

For more information, please consult the Design Manual for your particular process.
